# Monorepo Layout

```
ManageR2-System/          ← workspace root (npm workspaces)
  package.json            ← { "workspaces": ["apps/*"] }
  apps/
    web/                  ← Vite + React + TypeScript (npm workspace)
    api/                  ← ASP.NET Core C# (not an npm workspace)
  database/
    SP/                   ← all stored procedures (.sql files)
  .cursor/
    rules/
    skills/
```

## Where new code goes

| Type of change | Location |
|---|---|
| New React page or component | `apps/web/src/features/<domain>/` or `apps/web/src/shared/` |
| New API hook or client function | `apps/web/src/features/<domain>/api/` or `apps/web/src/api/` |
| New C# controller | `apps/api/ManageR2.Api/Features/<Domain>/` |
| New C# repository/service | `apps/api/ManageR2.Infrastructure/Features/<Domain>/` |
| New domain entity | `apps/api/ManageR2.Domain/Features/<Domain>/Entities/` |
| New stored procedure | `database/SP/sp_<Domain>_<Action>.sql` |
| New shared UI component | `apps/web/src/shared/components/<ComponentName>/` |

## Dependency rules

- `apps/web` and `apps/api` are fully independent workloads — no cross-app imports.
- Inside `apps/web/src/`: `app` → `features` → `shared` → `api`. No reverse direction.
- Inside `apps/api/`: `Api` → `Infrastructure` → `Domain`. No reverse direction.

## Running the monorepo

```bash
# All commands from repo root
npm run dev        # starts apps/web dev server (Vite)
npm run build      # production build of apps/web

# Backend — from apps/api/
dotnet build ManageR2.Backend.sln
dotnet run --project ManageR2.Api
```

## Never

- Add `node_modules/` to version control.
- Add a shared `package.json` dependency that only one workspace uses (install into that workspace).
- Add UI outside `apps/web/src/` — all UI lives in the React SPA.
